"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Treat risk factors for recurrent cellulitis, such as lymphedema, tinea pedis, and chronic venous insufficiency."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"f0a516",
"children":[
"Primary treatment for abscesses, furuncles, and carbuncles is incision and drainage. Gram stain and culture should be obtained when antibiotic administration is planned."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b733b4",
"children":[
"Skin abscesses may have higher cure rates when incision and drainage is accompanied by antibiotic treatment with ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus",
"children":[
"MRSA"
]
},
" coverage."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
